# AGENT RULES [CRITICAL]

**Rule 2 [CRITICAL]:** All Phoenix questions go to **PhoenixExpert** (auto-apply from the first message). Workflow: Confluence MCP (cloudId -> spaces -> search -> pages) + codebase, then call PhoenixExpert with both. **Code is primary, Confluence is secondary.**

**Rule 4 [IMPORTANT]:** Multi-agent collaboration via `.cursor/agents/` subagent specs, skills, and explicit handoffs (no Python `AgentRouter` in this workspace).

**Rule 5 [IMPORTANT]:** Use domain-specialist agents - PhoenixExpert (backend/services/Phoenix core), TestExpert (QA/automation), DevOpsExpert (CI/CD), PostmanExpert (Postman/APIs), BugFinder (Rule 32), ProductionDataReader (Rule PDR.0). Out-of-domain agents must NOT act without PhoenixExpert approval.

**Rule 8 [CRITICAL]:** Before any task, agents MUST consult **PhoenixExpert** (logic, approach, endpoints, validation, permissions). No task proceeds without approval. Applies to all agents.

**Rule 9 [IMPORTANT]:** When multiple agents are involved, PhoenixExpert has the final decision and MUST appear in the "Agents involved" footer.

**Rule 10 [IMPORTANT]:** Environment access uses the **environment-access** workflow (`.cursor/agents/environment-access.md`); browser/MCP only.

**Rule 11 [CRITICAL]:** IntegrationService before tasks - see Rule 0.3 in `core_rules.mdc`. This workspace has no `Cursor-Project/agents/` Python package; follow Jira/GitLab/MCP workflows from rules instead of importing `agents.*`.

**Rule 12 [IMPORTANT]:** Agents act autonomously **only when the task is unambiguous** (and Rule 8 is satisfied). If scope, environment, target, or acceptance criteria are missing or contradictory, STOP and ask clarifying questions before substantive work (Rule CONF.0). Confirm only for CRITICAL operations (destructive, production deployments).

**Rule 13 [IMPORTANT]:** Route work to the right specialist via Task tool / subagents / matching rules - no Python `AgentRouter`. Use `subagent_type: shell` (`.cursor/agents/shell.md`) for terminal/git multi-step work; fall back to `generalPurpose` if `shell` errors. Multi-repo Phoenix git sync follows `git-sync` / `git_sync_workflow.mdc`.

**Rule 17 [CRITICAL] - Collaboration patterns (one paragraph):** TestAgent / PostmanCollectionGenerator / GitLabUpdateAgent always consult PhoenixExpert first. EnvironmentAccessAgent goes through MCP/browser. Multi-agent flows are orchestrated by the parent agent (no Python router). Bug validation runs the Rule 32 BugFinder workflow (Confluence + codebase + 5-verdict matrix; see `agents/bug-validator.md`). All participating agents MUST appear in the "Agents involved" footer.

**Rule 34 [IMPORTANT]:** The `Cursor-Project/agents/` Python package was removed. Cursor behavior is defined in `.cursor/agents/*.md`, skills, and rules - not Python. Do NOT recreate the package or instruct `import agents.*` imports unless the user explicitly asks.
